# SMTP Configuration for Nodemailer - Contact Form Email Service
# These variables are REQUIRED for the contact form to send emails

# ============================================
# GMAIL SMTP CONFIGURATION (Recommended)
# ============================================

# Sender email address (the account sending emails)
FROM_EMAIL=webelio.leads@gmail.com

# SMTP Host (for Gmail)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com

# SMTP Port (587 for TLS/STARTTLS - for Gmail)
# Use 465 for SSL (less common)
SMTP_PORT=587

# SMTP Username (usually your Gmail address)
SMTP_USER=webelio.leads@gmail.com

# SMTP Password - IMPORTANT FOR GMAIL USERS:
# You MUST use an App Password, NOT your regular Gmail password
# Steps to generate App Password:
# 1. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 2. Enable 2-Step Verification first if not already enabled
# 3. Select "Mail" and "Windows Computer" (or your device)
# 4. Google will generate a 16-character app password
# 5. Copy that password here (remove spaces)
SMTP_PASS=your_app_password_here

# Recipient email (where contact form submissions are sent)
TO_EMAIL=recipient@example.com

# ============================================
# FOR OTHER SMTP PROVIDERS (Optional)
# ============================================
# Uncomment and update for SendGrid, Mailgun, AWS SES, etc.

# SendGrid Example:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.sendgrid.net
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=apikey
# SMTP_PASS=SG.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# AWS SES Example:
# SMTP_HOST=email-smtp.region.amazonaws.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=your_ses_username
# SMTP_PASS=your_ses_password

# ============================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================
# If emails are not sending:
# 1. Verify all 6 variables are set correctly
# 2. For Gmail: Ensure App Password is used (not regular password)
# 3. For Gmail: Ensure 2FA is enabled on your Google Account
# 4. Check the server logs for error messages
# 5. Test SMTP connection separately if needed
